Incident.Summary: CT 161642791. 8-10 y/o male harassed while using toilet

IncidentSuppNarrative.NarrativeText:
ATTACHMENTS:

- NCMEC Cybertip # 161642791

 

Narrative

On 5/23/23, the Maryland State Police Computer Crimes Section /Maryland Internet Crimes Against Children Task Force received NCMEC CyberTip # 161642791. The Cyber Tip, generated by TikTok indicated that a subject uploaded child pornography to the internet. The CyberTip was assigned to TFC Cooke for investigation.

 

The CyberTip provided the following information pertaining to the suspect:

Address: US
Email Address: foxxtrot5551@gmail.com
Screen/User Name: sailorthebeardie
IP Address: 71.200.182.206 (Login)
03-15-2023 11:37:28 UTC

 

The CyberTip contained 1 reported child pornography file. TFC Cooke reviewed the reported child pornography file and determined that it constitutes child pornography as it is defined under Maryland law. The file is described below:

 

Filename: 72294832774873608141616427910.mp4

Description: 1 minute color video of a fully nude white male (MALE #1), reasonably believed to be between 8 - 10 years of age, sitting on a toilet as another white male (MALE #2), reasonably believed to be between 13 - 15 years of age based on limited imagery of his leg and hand, kicks and harasses MALE #1. MALE #2 then focuses the camera on MALE #1's penis and holds his thumb and index finger up to the camera to appear as if he's measuring MALE #1's penis. MALE#1 is underdeveloped, devoid of pubic hair, and noticeably small compared to the size of the toilet and MALE#2.

 

The CyberTip indicated that the following IP address 71.200.182.206 (03-15-2023 00:48:49 UTC) was utilized to upload the reported contraband file.

 

TFC Cooke conducted a query of the upload IP address through an open-source database and determined that it is registered through Comcast and geo-locates generally to the Elkton area of Cecil County, Maryland.

 

TFC Cooke conducted a query of the email address (foxxtrot5551@gmail.com) associated with the suspect TikTok account through an open-source database and determined that it is registered to "Albert Long." A query through law-enforcement databases revealed multiple domestic and drug-related incidents associated with Albert Francis Long 4th (2/M DOB: 8/6/85). One such report detailed information regarding Albert's five children, all of which are juveniles in custody of Child Protective Services. TFC Cooke reached out to the reporting officer, Detective Tyler Shaff (Baltimore County Police Department - Crimes Against Children), who redirected to the CPS case agent, Mackenzie Cooke (Baltimore County Department of Social Services). A screenshot of MALE #1's face was provided to CPS Agent Cooke who advised that she recognized the individual as one of Albert Long's children and would provide complete details including his current foster home address as soon as possible.


On 5/26/23, Baltimore County CPS provided foster home information (Kenneth & Victoria Newkirk, 63 Winslow Dr, Elkton, MD 21921). On the same day, TFC Cooke and D/Sgt Zeller conducted a knock & talk at that address and made contact with both foster parents. Investigators identified both the victim and aggressor in the Tiktok video as brothers and two of the current foster children under the Newkirk's guardianship, Gavin Long (2/M 8/20/16, hereby known as G.L.) and Albert Long 5th (2/M 9/18/11, hereby known as A.L.), respectively. Knowing and voluntary consent was given to investigators to search A.L.'s cell phone - no contraband/suspicious activity observed. Both foster parents were cooperative and agreed to restrict A.L.'s internet/phone usage. G.L. was briefly interviewed while accompanied by both foster parents. The Cecil County State's Attorney's Office, Cecil County Child Advocacy Center, and Baltimore County Department of Social Services were updated - no criminal enforcement action/foster care alterations were recommended.
